                                                <h4 class="font-bold mrg10B mrg10T">Mobile Device Encrypted Audience Preference Data</h4>
                                                <p>Converge 360 Platformenables clients to utilize Encrypted Audience Encrypted Audience Preference Data via mobile devices such as smart phones and tablets. In many respects, the process we use in mobile is similar to those we've used for our online Encrypted Audience Preference Data. However, as cookies are less reliable on mobile devices, Converge 360 Platformuses statistical ID's to help us process mobile Encrypted Audience Preference Data. The use of statistical ID's does not impact Converge 360 Platformcurrent data retention rate.</p>
                                                <p>Converge 360 Platformhas also developed the Mobile Privacy Samurai - a privacy enhancing technology for the mobile advertising marketplace. Mobile Privacy Samurai utilizes similar noise injection techniques to those which are commonly used in various fields to protect anonymity. The Converge 360 PlatformMobile Privacy Samurai inserts additional noise into the mobile Encrypted Audience Encrypted Audience Preference Data we collect, which makes it significantly more difficult for anyone—including Converge 360 Platform—to re-identify any particular mobile User. For example, when a device is "tagged" with actual behaviors performed by a device, a set of recommended attributes are injected into the mobile device profile. This ensures the mobile device is immediately anonymized to protect the consumer, but still valuable and relevant for advertisers. For more information about Mobile Privacy Samurai, please contact Converge 360 Platformprivacy department at the information provided below.</p>
